|WKBClans: The Basics
|WKO-----------------

|YKOClans cost 1,000,000 coins to start, and require 200,000 coins in
monthly dues every 28 days. The Darkwind Clan Registrar automatically
deducts the fee from the leader's bank account each month and sends a
mudmail detailing the charge.

Clans can be formed at the Darkwind Clan Registrar office. Ask other
players for directions to this location. At the office you will
receive additional information about how to form a new clan.

Clans have two ranks: leader and member. There is exactly one leader,
and everyone else in a clan is a member.

Clans are ranked according to clan reputation.  Base clan reputation
is calculated from the average clan member level, clan member best
kill, and clan member charisma. Additional reputation can be gathered
through clan warfare. Every time a clan wins a war, the clan receives
additional reputation points based upon the reputation of the defeated
clan. Defeating a more reputable clan results in more reputation
points.

Clan warfare is only one aspect of clans. A clan isn't required to
engage in warfare. A war can only start if two clan leaders agree to
go to war. Thus, it's possible to have peaceful clans where the leader
never agrees to go to war.

Please see |YKB"help clans" |YKOfor a basic overview.
Please see |YKB"help clans war" |YKOfor warfare information.
